专访武汉“造谣”者之一谢琳卡医生：我的事情其实很简单，希望更多支援医护人员抗疫物资。
Interview with Dr. Sherinka, one of Wuhan's "disinformation" people: My business is actually very simple, hope that more support for medical personnel against the disease supplies.
张晓晖2020-02-01 14:20。
Zhang Xiaohui 2020-02-01 14: 20.
扫描二维码分享到朋友圈。
Scanning two-dimensional code to share with friends.
经济观察网 记者 张晓晖在武汉新冠肺炎疫情爆发初期，被武汉警方认为“造谣”而遭到警告的8位人士之一的华中科技大学同济医学院附属协和医院（下称“武汉协和医院”）肿瘤科医生谢琳卡，是最早向同事和亲友发出疫情警示的专业医生之一。
Zhang Xiaohui, an oncologist at the Tongji Medical School of Huazhong University of Science and Technology (hereinafter referred to as "Wuhan Concorde Hospital"), one of eight people warned by Wuhan police that the outbreak of Xinguan Pneumonia broke out in Wuhan, was one of the first doctors to alert colleagues and friends about the outbreak.
。
.
2019年12月30日晚上8点43，谢琳卡在她的肿瘤中心微信群内发出警示：。
At 8: 43 p.m. on December 30, 2019, Sherinka warned in a microphone group at her oncology center.
“各位老师好，我传染病院的师妹发在我们同门群里的消息：近期不要到华南海鲜市场去，那里现在发生了多人患不明原因肺炎（类似非典），今天我们医院已收治了多例华南海鲜市场的肺炎病人。
Dear teachers, my sister-in-law of the Infectious Diseases Hospital has sent messages to our fellow students: Don't go to the South China seafood market in the near future. There are many people suffering from unexplained pneumonia (similar to SARS).
大家注意戴口罩和通风。
Wear masks and ventilation.
”。
"
也正是这则关于疫情的警示，让谢琳卡医生陷入一场风波之中。
It was this warning about the outbreak that sent Dr. Shelinka into a sea of troubles.
。
.
在2020年1月初发生疫情最初的日子里，谢琳卡医生发出的上述警示，被武汉警方认定为“造谣”，并给谢琳卡医生打来电话“沟通”。
In the first days of the outbreak in early January 2020, Dr. Shelinka's warning was identified by Wuhan police as "disinformation" and a phone call was sent to Dr. Shelinka to "communicate."
。
.
一个月之后，疫情由武汉爆发并蔓延至全国，而谢琳卡医生也因为最早向公众发出警示，被众多网友致以敬意。
A month later, the outbreak spread from Wuhan to the whole country, and Dr Shelinka was honored for being the first to warn the public.
。
.
2月1日上午，经济观察网记者辗转联系上谢琳卡医生进行采访，采访结束后，谢琳卡医生就回到她的工作岗位，继续投入到对本次疫情的抗争中。
On the morning of February 1, a reporter from the Economic Watch network contacted Dr. Shelinka for an interview. After the interview, Dr. Sherinka returned to her job and continued to fight the epidemic.
。
.
以下是对话实录：。
Dialogue Script 2 2
经济观察网；先向您致敬，您是最早发出疫情警示的武汉8位“造谣者”之一。
Economic Observation Network: First of all, I would like to pay tribute to you, you are one of the first eight Wuhan "disinformation."
。
.
谢琳卡医生：最近我确实也接到很多媒体朋友的电话。
Dr. Shelinka: I did get a lot of phone calls from my media friends recently.
作为医生，我很少跟媒体有接触。
As a doctor, I have little contact with the media.
这个事情其实没有什么很特别的，只是因为现在舆论的这个导向是这样子（指要求武汉对8名造谣者平反的舆论发酵）。
There is nothing special about this matter, just because the current direction of public opinion is like this (refers to the public opinion that Wuhan to rehabilitate 8 disinformation people ferment).
。
.
经济观察网：可以跟我们说说事情的经过吗？。
Economic Watch: Can you tell us something about it?
谢琳卡医生：当初也没有很特别，只是在群里发出了一个很简单的预警。
Dr. Shelinka: It wasn't special either. It was a very simple warning in the group.
。
.
经济观察网：我们看到12月30日您在肿瘤中心的群里发出了一则警示，称华南海鲜市场有不明的肺炎。
ECONOMIC OBSERVATION NETWORK: We saw a warning on Dec. 30 from a group at the center of the tumor that there was unexplained pneumonia in the South China seafood market.
。
.
谢琳卡医生：那个是12月30日晚上8点多，当时我只是在医生自己的内部群里面警示了一下。
Dr. Shelinka: It was more than 8: 00 p.m. on December 30th, and I was just alerting the doctor in his inner circle.
因为我们单位距离华南海鲜市场非常之近，我们就在旁边，又是肿瘤中心，肿瘤中心都是肿瘤患者，抵抗力都很低。
Because our unit is very close to the South China seafood market, we are next to the tumor center, tumor center is tumor patients, very low resistance.
还有很多同事居住在单位附近，也就是这个区域（指华南海鲜市场）附近。
There are also many colleagues living in the vicinity of the unit, that is, this area (refers to the South China Seafood Market).
如果这个事件是个风险事件的话，大家来来往往被感染的风险就会比较高。
If this event is a risk event, the risk of people coming and going will be higher.
。
.
当时就在群里给大家预警了一下，提醒大家至少把口罩戴起来，减少传播的可能性。
At that time in the group gave everyone an early warning, to remind everyone to at least wear masks, reduce the possibility of transmission.
就是这个事情，第二天这个消息就变成了满城飞，当时这个事件我知道是一个真实的事件，只是不知道后续的量会有多少，会变成什么样子，我们没有第一手数据，只是预警。
The next day the news turned into a full city, and I knew it was a real event, but we had no first-hand data on how much it would take and what it would look like.
。
.
经济观察网：发出警示之后呢？。
Economic Watch: After the Warning?
谢琳卡医生：后来事情就有点发酵。
Dr. Shelinka: Then things sort of fermented.
也没有很特殊的，说被抓到公安局去，没有这样子，公安局只是打来一个电话，跟我说了一下。
There is nothing special about being caught at the police station. Without this, the police just called and told me.
。
.
就是这么简单的一件事情。
It's such a simple thing.
。
.
经济观察网：您发出警示之后，您和您的同事有无被感染新冠肺炎？您的这个警示是不是对她们起了很大的作用？。
ECONOMIC OBSERVATION NETWORK: Did you and your colleagues get infected with New Crown Pneumonia after you issued the alert? Did this alert really help them?
谢琳卡医生：后来说的话，我的很多同事确实开始在家里面先预防、购买口罩之类的，然后自己出门都戴着口罩。
Dr. Shelinka: As I said later, many of my co-workers actually started taking precautions at home, buying masks, and then wearing masks when they went out.
我不知道有没有帮助到别人，但是大家肯定都提高了警惕，特别是住在附近的同事，都没有让家里的老人出去，小孩送到比较偏远的地方去。
I don't know if it helped, but everyone was definitely on the lookout, especially the colleagues who lived nearby, who didn't let the old people out and send the kids to more remote places.
我觉得多少还是有一点点作用吧。
I think there's a little bit of a difference.
。
.
经济观察网：您现在的工作状态如何？。
Economic Observation Network: How well do you work now?
谢琳卡医生：按现在这个事情来看，在隔离病房肯定是要穿防护服。
Dr. Shelinka: As things stand now, protective clothing must be worn in the isolation ward.
我们后来还是有很多门诊医生，因为莫名原因好像没有接触到感染源却被感染了。
We still had a lot of out-patient doctors because for some reason they didn't seem to touch the source of the infection but got infected.
我现在还在住院部，本来有派去门诊，但是我自己中间有感冒和咳嗽的症状，就不太适合到门诊去。
I'm still in the inpatient department, and I was sent to the clinic, but I had my own symptoms of colds and coughs, which made them less suitable for outpatient visits.
。
.
经济观察网：您自己也有感冒咳嗽症状？希望您平安。
Economic Observation Network: You also have cold cough symptoms? Hope you are safe.
。
.
谢琳卡医生：我们医生平时也是非常繁忙，身体状况可能处于亚健康状态，不是特别好。
Dr. Shelinka: Our doctors are usually very busy, they may be in a subnormal state of health, not particularly well.
。
.
之前我比较抵触这个事情，我觉得大家应该更多的支持疫情物资提供，防护服口罩这些事情，现在想想还是说清楚比较好，免得外界老是打电话来找我问这件事。
Before I am more resistant to this matter, I think we should more support epidemic supplies, protective clothing masks these things, now think clearly better, so that the outside world always call me to ask about this matter.
。
.
采访结束之后，谢琳卡医生还发来了她对这个事情经过的说明，全文如下：。
After the interview, Dr. Shelinka sent a note describing her experience of the incident, which read as follows:
2019年对于我来说过的并不容易。
2019 has not been an easy year for me.
工作忙碌、年中病了一场，更觉得生命可贵。
Busy work, mid-year illness, but also feel valuable life.
没想到年底又来了一场风波。
I didn't expect another storm at the end of the year.
。
.
虽然我是一名乳腺肿瘤科的医生，但曾经出身于感染病学专业。
Although I am a doctor in the Department of Mammary Oncology, I was born in the Department of Infectious Diseases.
2019年底，在我们感染科同门群里有师妹预警，有多例表现类似的不明原因肺炎患者出现，并且都有华南海鲜市场接触史。
At the end of 2019, there was a sibling alert in our infection ward, several cases of similarly unexplained pneumonia, and all had a history of exposure to the South China seafood market.
我们肿瘤中心正座落于华南海鲜市场附近、好多同事都住在旁边，并且我们的肿瘤患者抵抗力低下。
Our oncology center is located near the South China Seafood Market, where many of our colleagues live, and our cancer patients have low resistance.
本着防患于未然的考虑，我在中心内部群里建议大家做好防护。
As a precaution, I advised you to take precautions in the inner circle of the centre.
没想到被截屏、第二天一睁眼居然成了网红。
Did not expect to be cut screen, the next day open his eyes turned into a net red.
我一个普通医生哪里经历过这种情况，心里压力确实大。
I'm a general practitioner who's been through this and I'm really stressed out.
。
.
我想澄清一点的是，当时公安局的警察同志确实有跟我打电话（只是打了个电话），但是态度很客气，我当时也和警察同志说了，我是一线医生，我们单位在旁边，风险高，希望大家多小心，提高警惕。
I would like to make it clear that the police comrades at the time did call me (just by phone), but they were very polite and I told the police that I was a front-line doctor.
。
.
整个事件当中，收获了很多朋友的关心，包括很多患者的关心。
Throughout the incident, a lot of friends have learned to care, including many patients care.
我也很感谢我们感染病学同门们的预警，他们中也有人感染，正在隔离中。
I am also grateful to our fellow infectors for their early warning that some of them are infected and in isolation.
也感谢我们全国各地的兄弟姐妹来武汉支援。
Also thanks to our brothers and sisters from all over the country to Wuhan support.
“预警”乃医者本分，如果当时的预警真的帮助到了一部分人免于感染，我也是非常高兴的。
"Early warning" is a doctor's job, if the early warning really helped some people avoid infection, I am also very happy.
感谢警察同志没有难为我。
Thanks to the cops for not bothering me.
。
.
最近每位医生护士都很辛苦，我们中心抽调了好多医生和护士去了发热门诊、病房，留守的医生值班也是一个人负责好几层楼。
Recently, every doctor and nurse is very hard, our center transferred a lot of doctors and nurses to the fever clinic, ward, the doctor on duty is also a person in charge of several floors.
现在医护确实太辛苦、物资紧缺，希望发放物资的部门加速流程，即使有些物资也许不符合医学标准，分给我们也行啊，至少比完全没有好，留下来存在库房只能长霉。
It is true that medical care is too hard and supplies are in short supply, and it is hoped that departments that distribute materials will speed up the process, even if some of them may not meet medical standards.
。
.
